Breakfast Technical Briefing on Medical Equipment Stocks -- Hologic, Wright Medical, Edwards Lifesciences, and Stryker








 Friday, July 28, 2017 General News




















 Font : A-A+ 






















NEW YORK, July 28, 2017 /PRNewswire/ --
If you want a Stock Review on HOLX, WMGI, EW, or SYK then come over to http://dailystocktracker.com/register/ 





and sign up for your free customized report today. DailyStockTracker.com has issued research reports on Hologic Inc. (NASDAQ: HOLX), Wright Medical Group N.V. (NASDAQ: WMGI), Edwards Lifesciences Corp. (NYSE: EW), and Stryker Corp. (NYSE: SYK). Companies 




in the Medical Appliances and Equipment space are engaged in the manufacture of medical instruments such as dental and surgical appliances. Most of the time, they are structured as corporations. Daily Stock Tracker published free research reports on these stocks today at:
	http://dailystocktracker.com/register/
Hologic 
Marlborough, Massachusetts headquartered Hologic Inc.'s shares dropped 1.55%, closing Thursday's trading session at $44.44. The stock recorded a trading volume of 1.86 million shares. Shares of the Company have advanced 10.77% since the start of this year. The stock is trading 6.98% above its 200-day moving average. Additionally, shares of Hologic, which develops, manufactures, and supplies diagnostics products, medical imaging systems, and surgical products for women in the US, Europe, the Asia-Pacific, and internationally, have a Relative Strength Index (RSI) of 45.67.  
On July 05th, 2017, Hologic announced that it plans to release its financial results for Q3 FY17 on August 02nd, 2017, after the market closes. In conjunction with the release, management will host a conference call at 4:30 p.m. ET. A live webcast of the call may be accessed on the Company's website. See our free and comprehensive research report on HOLX at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=HOLX
Wright Medical 
On Thursday, shares in Amsterdam, the Netherlands headquartered Wright Medical Group N.V. recorded a trading volume of 1.23 million shares, which was above their three months average volume of 1.01 million shares. The stock rose 1.58%, ending the day at $28.37. The Company's shares have advanced 7.34% in the past month and 23.46% on an YTD basis. The stock is trading above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages by 4.76% and 7.66%, respectively. Furthermore, shares of Wright Medical, which designs, manufactures, markets, and sells extremities and biologics products in the US, Europe, Middle-East, Africa, and internationally, have an RSI of 64.45.  
On June 30th, 2017, research firm Cantor Fitzgerald initiated an 'Overweight' rating on the Company's stock, with a target price of $33 per share.
On July 05th, 2017, Wright Medical announced that it will host a conference call on August 02nd, 2017, at 3:30 p.m. CT to discuss the Company's operating results for its Q2 ended June 25th, 2017. Operating results will be released at 3:00 p.m. CT on that same day. A simultaneous webcast of the call will be available on the Company's corporate website. WMGI free research report is just a click away at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=WMGI
Edwards Lifesciences 
Irvine, California headquartered Edwards Lifesciences Corp.'s stock finished the day 0.65% higher at $116.36. A total volume of 3.53 million shares was traded, which was above their three months average volume of 1.20 million shares. Shares of the Company have advanced 6.10% in the previous three months and 24.18% on an YTD basis. The stock is trading above its 200-day moving average by 14.96%. Additionally, shares of Edwards Lifesciences, which provides products and technologies to treat structural heart disease and critically ill patients worldwide, have an RSI of 47.46.  
On July 26th, 2017, Edwards Lifesciences reported financial results for the quarter ended June 30th, 2017. Sales for Q2 2017 were $841.8 million; adjusted earnings per share grew 42.1% to $1.08; gross profit margin was 74.9%; selling, general, and administrative expenses increased to $243.8 million; and R&D investments increased to $134.4 million. Cash, cash equivalents, and short-term investments totaled $1.13 billion at June 30th, 2017. Additionally, total debt was $1.02 billion.
On July 27th, 2017, research firm Stifel reiterated its 'Buy' rating on the Company's stock with an increase of the target price from $118 a share to $130 a share. Sign up for your complimentary report on EW at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=EW
Stryker 
Shares in Kalamazoo, Michigan headquartered Stryker Corp. ended yesterday's session 1.17% lower at $144.05. The stock recorded a trading volume of 1.47 million shares, which was above its three months average volume of 1.08 million shares. The Company's shares have advanced 3.20% in the last one month, 6.41% over the previous three months, and 20.23% since the start of this year. The stock is trading 1.70% and 12.61% above its 50-day and 200-day moving averages, respectively. Moreover, shares of Stryker, which together with its subsidiaries, operates as a medical technology company, have an RSI of 52.07.
On June 30th, 2017, research firm Cantor Fitzgerald initiated a 'Neutral' rating on the Company's stock, with a target price of $153 per share. Register for free on DailyStockTracker.com and download the latest research report on SYK at:
http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=SYK
--
